~ When exported to .csv (comma-separated values), my script will ignore anything within the same line that starts with '~'. .csv files go from left to right, and after the last entry of the row, it creates a new line.
~ Make sure to put any data that is after edge width to be after ~, otherwise, my script will try to parse that data and might crash.
~ Unit is meter unless otherwise stated
